  "title": "Genetics of nonnodulation in groundnut (Arachis hypogaea L.). Studies with single and mixed Rhizobium strains",
  "abstract": "Genetic studies of nonnodulation in groundnut were carried out in a cross, NC 17×PI 259747, with a single Rhizobium strain, NC 92, and a native Rhizobium population.\r\nThe normal nodulation of the parents, F1 generations and backcross progenies, and the F2 segregation for nodulation and nonnodulation confirmed that nonnodulation in groundnut is controlled by two duplicate recessive genes",
